More generally, even when the condition on \(\mathbf{\widehat{\beta}}\) is not satisfied and if \(\mathbf{y}\) is negative, we show in Appendix B that for zero-mean and symmetrically distributed covariates, i.e., \(\mathbb{E}\left[\mathbf{x}\right]=0\) and \((\mathbf{x}\sim-\mathbf{x})\), adversarial training has approximately the same solution as

\[\min_{\mathbf{\beta}}\frac{1}{n}\sum_{i=1}^{n}|y_{i}-\mathbf{x}_{i}^{\top}\mathbf{\beta}|^ {2}+\big{(}\delta\|\mathbf{\beta}\|_{*}+\tfrac{1}{n}\mathbf{s}^{\top}\mathbf{y}\big{)}^{2},\]

