**Intuitive explanation for abrupt transitions.** To get insight into why the abrupt transition occurs we present the case where \(n=1\), i.e., the dataset has a single data point \((\mathbf{x},y)\), where \(y=1\) and \(\|\mathbf{x}\|_{2}=1\). We can write \(R^{\text{adv}}(\mathbf{\beta};\delta,\|\cdot\|_{2})=(\mathcal{L}(\mathbf{\beta}))^{2}\), where

